<h2>Modifying settings in Messages</h2>
<h3>Automatic forwarding</h3>

<p>Each participant can use the automatic forwarding feature to send an
email message to an email address of his or her choosing upon receipt
of each message in the Messages tool. To enable this feature:</p>

<ol><li>In the <a href="content.hlp?docId=arcc">menubar</a> of the relevant site, choose
<strong><code>Messages</code></strong>.

<br /><br />
</li><li>Click <strong><code>Settings</code></strong>, set "Auto Forward Messages" to
<strong><code>Yes</code></strong>, and enter your preferred email address.

<br /><br />
</li><li>Click <strong><code>Save Settings</code></strong>.</li></ol>


<h3>Send Cc options</h3>

<p><strong>Note:</strong> To complete these procedures, you must be
assigned a role having the necessary permissions.  To determine your
role, follow the directions in <a href="content.hlp?docId=arbu">Participant roles</a>.  For a basic understanding of roles and
permissions, see <a href="content.hlp?docId=arax">Permissions and roles: Overview</a>.</p>

<p>By default, when composing a message, site participants can select the
<strong><code>Send Cc</code></strong> option to forward a copy of the message to the
recipient's authorized email address.  </p>




<p>Users with an administrative role (instructors, assistants, and
project owners) can enable or disable the Send Cc option as
follows:</p> 

<ol><li>In the site's menubar, choose <strong><code>Messages</code></strong>.

<br /><br />
</li><li>Click <strong><code>Settings</code></strong>.

<br /><br />
</li><li>Next to "Allow sending copies to recipients' email address(es)",
choose the desired option.

<br /><br />
</li><li>Click <strong><code>Save Settings</code></strong>.
</li></ol> 

<h3>Hiding custom groups</h3>

<p>Users with an administrative role (instructors, assistants, and
project owners) can choose to remove/hide custom <a href="content.hlp?docId=atcs">groups</a> from the "To" field. To hide a custom group:</p>

<ol><li>From the site's menubar, choose <strong><code>Messages</code></strong>.

<br /><br />
</li><li>Click <strong><code>Settings</code></strong>.

<br /><br />
</li><li>Next to "Groups hidden in To field", from the "Add Group"
drop-down box, choose the group you would like to hide.

<br /><br />
</li><li>Click <strong><code>Save Settings</code></strong>.</li></ol> 




